  <result aggregation-status="1" type="1">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Annual Output Results</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. National agreement on core objectives and areas of the political reform in Lesotho collectively agreed  
2. National dialogue process and outcome inclusive of security vision with broader security sector buy-in, participation and guaranteed safety assurances
3. A comprehensive national Communications Strategy in place to support public engagement on the national dialogues</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. National Reforms Roadmap proposed by Govt
2. No existing inter-agency vision and strategy
3.Limited public knowledge of political reforms and goals in Lesotho</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. National dialogue and reform process and outcome document collectively agreed by, GoL political parties; traditional leaders; civil society (youth/women organizations); religious leaders; academia; media and citizens of Lesotho, and supported by development partners.
2. Comprehensive security sector vision and strategy developed and affected officers rehabilitated and reintegrated
3. Communication strategy developed, and rolled out through use of different information and communication platforms</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	An all-inclusive participatory national dialogue and reforms process resulted in a national agreement on the reforms content and options for implementation, safeguarded by a legal and institutional framework. This becomes the basis for national reconciliation, sustainable peace and a reforms path for democratic governance in Lesotho. The outcome document was endorsed by governing coalition partners, opposition parties in and outside parliament, religious groups, civil society organisations, professional associations, academia, the media, women&#x2019;s organisations, the youth groups, people living with disabilities, farmers and herders unions, trade unions and Royalty.
2.	A strong foundation for a comprehensive national security sector vision, strategy and policy was established with reduced tension and enhanced participation of security sector in the reforms process. This included policy engagement and concurrence with sector high command; counselling/psychosocial support to 1,200 security members; completion of UN-Human Rights Due Diligence Policy Assessment and; 500 Trainers on key security aspects.
3.	The development and operationalisation of a communication strategy for national dialogue and reforms resulted in development of digital media strategy, Information and Communication Materials and training of critical teams leading to increased access to coherent information on the national dialogue and reform process as well as mobilisation of public to effectively participate in the in-district consultations.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
